# FlexNetOS Workspace Agent Contract

This is the first file to read when working under `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS`.
The workspace root is a hollow orchestration area, not a monorepo. Real
implementation work belongs in independent peer repositories under `src/`.

## Canonical Repositories

- `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/yazelix`: FlexNetOS-owned Yazelix foundation repo.
- `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/meta`: FlexNetOS-owned meta repo.
- `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/envctl`: environment authority repo.
- `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/flexnetos_runner`: release runner/provenance repo.
- `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/upstream/<owner>/<repo>`: upstream evidence mirrors only.

Yazelix and meta are both organization-owned peer repos in this workspace. Do
not place them under `src/upstream/` unless creating a separate comparison clone.

## Meta Control-Plane Rules

`/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/meta` is the control plane for the FlexNetOS
peer-repo fleet. Treat the Meta KB, GitKB metadata, and the original FlexNetOS
Meta project set as additive-only upgrade targets. Do not downgrade, reset,
delete, remove, overwrite, or replace Meta control-plane state unless the
affected state is archived first and the archive is compressed under a reviewed
workspace evidence path such as `var/lib/codex-runtime-gate/archives`,
`artifacts`, `snapshots`, or `var/log/raw`.

The original Meta project set includes `loop_lib`, `meta_plugin_protocol`,
`meta_core`, `meta_git_lib`, `loop_cli`, `meta_cli`, `meta_git_cli`,
`meta_project_cli`, `meta_rust_cli`, and `meta_mcp`. Add-on repos such as
`agent`, `claude-plugins`, `codex-plugins`, and `meta-plugins` are still
FlexNetOS Meta org repos and follow the same archive-first rule for destructive
or downgrade-like work.

## Codex and Yazelix Runtime Invariants

These host/runtime surfaces are active control paths, not incidental local
files. Do not change, regenerate, prune, or "clean up" them until their owner
and current generated state have been identified from live proof.

- Yazelix/Nix profile binary ownership: `yzx`, `rtk`, `codex`, `claude`, and
  `git-kb` are intended to resolve through `/home/flexnetos/.nix-profile` or
  documented local compatibility links into Nix store-owned binaries. Verify
  profile/local frontdoors with `readlink -f` before claiming installed runtime
  state, and keep Codex app-server checks such as `codex app-server daemon
  version` and `codex doctor --all` with that profile-owned binary context.
- Codex config layers are distinct. `/home/flexnetos/.codex/config.toml` is
  active runtime state, `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/.codex/config.toml` is the
  workspace control-plane mirror/source, and `src/envctl/agent-env.yaml` is the
  envctl generation input. Keep plugin/MCP ownership single-path; do not create
  overlapping Codex plugin or MCP inventories.
- Plugin marketplace caches and temp bundles are not authority. Do not rebuild,
  re-enable, or infer active runtime plugin state from
  `~/.codex/.tmp/plugins/`, cached marketplace bundles, `openai-curated`
  listings, or repo-local plugin caches. If the active runtime should stay
  narrow, preserve removals of noisy marketplace/plugin surfaces such as
  `superhuman`, `digitalocean`, and duplicate command/skill inventories unless
  the owner explicitly asks to restore them.
- Root Codex lifecycle hooks from the pre-clean-room state are retired. Keep
  `features.hooks = false` for that retired root hook family until a new
  clean-room lifecycle-hook design is deliberately introduced. Do not restore
  `.codex/hooks.json`, `.codex/hooks/`, raw `.old` files, or archived
  lifecycle-hook sources from `_quarantine/` as a workaround.
- `_quarantine/` and archived packs are evidence only. They may explain prior
  state, but they are not active sources of truth and must not be copied back
  into live control paths without a fresh archive-first review and explicit
  owner decision.
- Yazelix profile/runtime ownership is the launch authority. The visible
  FlexNetOS Agent launcher should execute `/home/flexnetos/.nix-profile/bin/yzx`
  and set `YAZELIX_LAYOUT_OVERRIDE` to
  `/home/flexnetos/.nix-profile/configs/zellij/layouts/flexnetos_agent_workspace.kdl`
  unless the owner deliberately changes the install route. That layout path
  should resolve through the Nix profile into the Yazelix package source/runtime.
- Repo source under `src/yazelix/...` is the product-development input for repo
  fixes, not the active launcher path. Consume source changes through the
  Yazelix/Nix profile owner before claiming installed behavior changed.
  Generated layouts under `~/.local/share/yazelix` are runtime proof only.
- The FlexNetOS Agent launcher is additive. The stock Yazelix Mars desktop entry
  remains generator-owned and should not carry FlexNetOS custom layout state;
  the visible FlexNetOS Agent entry is the custom-layout consumer.
- Claude and Codex status widgets are separate runtime signals. Do not treat
  Claude as purged merely because legacy `.claude/commands` wrappers changed;
  verify `claude --version`, `.claude/skills`, and the Yazelix `widget_tray`
  before removing or declaring missing Claude status behavior.
- Historical `WORKLOG.md` and `LOCAL_WORKAROUNDS.md` entries may describe stale
  intermediate states. Prefer the latest dated entry plus live proof when they
  conflict, especially for hooks, Codex versions, desktop entries, and generated
  Yazelix layouts.

## Mandatory Start Procedure

Before editing any peer repo:

1. Read this file, `WORKSPACE_LAYOUT.md`, `WORKLOG.md`, and
   `LOCAL_WORKAROUNDS.md`.
2. Read the target repo's `AGENTS.md`, `README.md`, and relevant subsystem docs.
3. Snapshot branch, HEAD SHA, remote URL, and dirty status.
4. Use Beads when the repo has `.beads/`; create or claim a focused issue for
   new defects before changing code.
5. Keep execution packs as guidance only. Do not implement inside pack
   directories, and do not let pack artifacts satisfy task gates by themselves.
6. Do not mark work complete without live proof from repo state, installed tool
   state, envctl tables, generated artifacts, runner/provenance output, GitKB,
   meta, Beads, or command logs.
7. Do not run Nix validation probes in parallel.

## Yazelix Foundation Rules

Yazelix is the first foundation dependency for this workspace. For Yazelix
product work, use `/home/flexnetos/FlexNetOS/src/yazelix` as the source of truth.
Use its repo-owned tools, including `nix develop`, `yzx dev test`,
`yzx dev test --sweep`, and `yzx_repo_validator`.

This product-source rule does not make repo source an installed launcher,
layout, or binary frontdoor. Installed FlexNetOS Agent behavior must still be
proven through `/home/flexnetos/.nix-profile/bin/yzx`, the profile-owned
`YAZELIX_LAYOUT_OVERRIDE`, and generated runtime state.

Installed `yzx` proves installed-runtime behavior only. It does not prove a repo
fix unless the repo source changed and repo validators passed.

Read `LOCAL_WORKAROUNDS.md` before running `yzx desktop install`, editing
`~/.local/share/yazelix`, or changing desktop launcher state. The current host
has a documented local launcher workaround that generated installs can overwrite.

Do not run `nix profile add`, `nix profile upgrade`, `home-manager switch`,
`yzx desktop install`, or any command that mutates an installed launcher/profile
as a build proof. Profiles, Home Manager generations, and desktop entries are
consumers. First build and validate the source package outputs in isolation,
then deliberately choose the single install owner that will consume them.

## Local State vs Product Fixes

Files under `~/.config`, `~/.local/share`, Nix profiles, and generated runtime
directories are evidence or host-local workarounds unless a repo generator owns
them. A real product fix must land in the owning repo source, include Beads
state when applicable, and pass the owning validation lane.

When local state is touched, update `LOCAL_WORKAROUNDS.md`, `WORKLOG.md`, or
`COMMAND_LEDGER.csv` with the command, proof, and remaining product gap.

## Forbidden Shortcuts

- Do not infer missing runtime packages from ambient `PATH`; Yazelix packages
  tools inside its runtime/dev environment.
- Do not overwrite generated configs without first identifying the generator.
- Do not call a workaround a fix.
- Do not advance task IDs based on files created only in recovery or execution
  packs.

